From c6040b9e81c06859fa8f755f2c8cfbc0148b98a5 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Slick <slick@slicksync.local>
Date: Sun, 12 Jul 2026 08:19:15 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] fix: Now Playing never detecting genuine active viewing

isActivelyWatching() required the watch-state hash to change between
two consecutive 5-minute polls, falling back to time-based freshness
only on the very first observation after a restart. This assumed
continuous lastWatched updates during playback, but Nuvio only writes
a checkpoint on pause/stop/background - during genuine continuous
viewing the hash often doesn't change between polls, so the
comparison concluded 'user stopped' on every non-first poll, a false
negative that could keep Now Playing from ever appearing for an
entire session.

Removed the hash-comparison entirely (also removes the now-dead
in-memory previousWatchStates Map, which was wiped on every container
restart anyway - a second, smaller reliability problem). Relies on
time-based freshness alone, matching what already works correctly for
the recentActivity/MovieWatchHistory pipeline.

Bump to 1.9.26, changelog entry added.
---
 client/public/changelog.json   | 10 +++++++
 package.json                   |  2 +-
 server/utils/sessionTracker.js | 51 ++++++++++------------------------
 3 files changed, 26 insertions(+), 37 deletions(-)

diff --git a/client/public/changelog.json b/client/public/changelog.json
index c2bb913..0e12410 100644
--- a/client/public/changelog.json
+++ b/client/public/changelog.json
@@ -1,4 +1,14 @@
 [
+  {
+    "version": "1.9.26",
+    "date": "2026-07-12",
+    "title": "Fix Now Playing never detecting genuine active viewing",
+    "bugFixes": [
+      "isActivelyWatching() required the watch-state hash (lastWatched/position) to change between two consecutive 5-minute polls before counting an item as 'still being watched', falling back to a time-based check only on the very first observation after a server restart. That assumed the provider updates lastWatched continuously during playback - but Nuvio only writes a checkpoint on pause/stop/background (established earlier this session), so during genuine continuous viewing the hash frequently doesn't change between polls at all, and the comparison concluded 'user stopped' on every poll after the first - a false negative that could make 'Now Playing' never appear for an entire active session. Now relies on time-based freshness alone (lastWatched within 7.5 minutes), trading a small staleness tail after playback genuinely stops for reliably detecting that it's actually happening."
+    ],
+    "features": [],
+    "miscChores": []
+  },
   {
     "version": "1.9.25",
     "date": "2026-07-12",
